VCatch Hariharan's soulful voice with the palace as a backdrop. Flautist Pravin Godkhindi will perform along with Hariharan at the ghazal evening, Ghazal at Palace on Sunday, December 17.Aalap Events and Media is organising the evening of music where Hariharan will also felicitate the promising flautist from Karnataka, Pravin Godkhindi.A composer, vocalist, actor, tabla and harmonium player all rolled into one, Pravin learnt playing the bansuri in the Kirana gharana style from his father, Pandit Venkatesh Godkhindi.Hariharan, of the Colonial Cousins fame, will present an evening of ghazals in Bangalore. He was inspired in his teen years by the undisputed maestro Mehdi Hassan and developed a passion for this form. He's well-known for his affinity for ghazals, which he believes offer "immense scope for innovation".The concert is at 6.30 p.m at Palace Grounds (Mount Carmel College entrance). Tickets are priced at Rs. 1,099, 599, and 399. They are available at Foodworld, Reliance World outlets, Health and Glow, and online atwww.indiaplaza.in.For details call 080- 64519707/99001 49706.Bottom Template Starts
